<br>
We have 5 gnome magicians, currently around lvl 17-20.  From what I have seen so far it rocks.  <br>
<br>
We had our armor quests done for all 5 by lvl 10-13 for the group, and went to Paludal caverns.  (now we have a lime-green uniform for the army)<br>
<br>
We were taking Patog Phlarg fiends before the last memeber hit 12, and rolled into 16 easily (about 1-2 hours per level, constant pulling).  Due to carelessness we had 1 death, and 4 people crudded simultaneously before we got camp set up.  Bind wounds skill maxxed for several members fighting the crud, but even using all mana on bandages we could still take fiends with pets alone.<br>
<br>
At lvl 16 we got bored/annoyed with the crowds at PC so we moved to the Warrens.  We've taken the king once in 2 tries  (first try he spawned on us with shaman, and we have a 4-pull incoming).  The HT tends to kill a magician so its important to get pets in to soak that first.<br>
<br>
My questions/comments.  If anyone else has tried this...<br>
As an FYI I've solo'd mages to the mid-30's but haven't tried an all mage group before so a lot of what I knew on the what/where to go was for solo'ing. <br>
<br>
1) We haven't had anything even vaguely resembling strategy to date.  Often we fail even the most elementary pet control, fail to get all the pets on the same target, etc.  This hasn't really hurt us much, but I suspect it will.  Anyone know at what level this will start to be important?<br>
<br>
2) We used water pets up til lvl 16, and have been using water or fire now.  At lvl 20 we will have all the pets to try a mix.  Any suggestions on a good mix of pets?  Again it hasn't mattered much up til now, but might at some point.  I'm curious to see the stunning power of 5 air pets for example.<br>
<br>
3) Fortunately we have a member who has a high level alt, as we have been gaining levels faster than cash, and have needed some loans for spells (and we aren't even getting all the spells).  Any suggestions for quick cash at or after lvl 20 (which we wil probably get soon)?  We haven't bothered with twinking, but getting 40-50 plat worth of spells for 5 players get very costly very quick<br>
<br>
4) We're leaving warrens tonight and moving to Stonebrunt to try to hit 20 on everyone.  Can anyone suggest some hunting for a massive number of pulls at or after lvl 20?  The way things have gone so far we don't want a camp, we need half a zone or so to get enough pulls to keep the fights going.  We tend to have 1-2 pullers running near constantly so we need quite a few spawn to keep the group busy.<br>
<br>
5)  Although we haven't had many problems in the way of &quot;slowdown&quot; we will want to gain our focus items at some point.  At what level could a pack of 5 magician roll through Najena without stopping (I'm guessing 20-24sih but I'm not certain how all the gobbie magicians and darkbones will go)<br>
<br>
6) We're planning on having one member focus on research (to aid in spell gathering at higher levels).  Does anyone else have any suggestions along these lines to take advantage of our assets?  <br>
<br>
Riemann, conceiver of the Pet Squad  <br>
(with Nabace, Maggpie, Nicepie, and Gnik)<br>
<br>
PS we tend to only play a day or 2 a week, so we probably won't be lvl 60 and ready for raids this month. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
PPS Yes, we do get a lot of comments when 5 gnomes in identical robes with identical pets charge through a zone. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uizarek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izarek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#333333>(8/16/02 9:34:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=409.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet squad?</span><hr size=1> 1) Strategy is important depending on the zone.  In places where mobs are social and you have a high chance of adds (practically anywhere in Luclin, Kunark isn't as bad) you have to start now.  In your late 20s its definitely a requirement.<br>
<br>
2) Mix of pets: Depends on situations.  If you get lots of adds, I would make sure you have at least 2 earth pets.  These people will be your crowd control.  If pet health is an issue, use water: faster regen.  If not use fire.  Once you have 2 or 3 fire pets being the main tanks, they DS will eat things up.  If you do a lot of single pulls, use air.  3 air pets stunning won't see much damage, will taunt really well and interrupt casters.<br>
<br>
3) At your level you need to be killing lots of mobs that drop fine steel or bronze weapons.  You could try:<br>
- Najena - Great place to start your epic and get items for your focus item quests<br>
- Unrest<br>
- WK/NK bandits - Wipeout all the camps.  Turn in sashes in S.Qeynos. Also kill wisps for GLS quest in NK.<br>
- Sol A - Great loot.  Lots of mobs in their mid 20s though.<br>
<br>
4) SolA or Mistmoore have a large concentration of mobs.  Very trainy zones.  Not very busy.<br>
<br>
5)  You'd be better off farming Najena slowly at your level, get exp and loot.  You should be able to do most of the zone with 5 of you.  I soloed most of it at 31 I think.  5 mages in their low 20s should do fine.<br>
<br>
6) Save up your money so your researcher can buy research points.  Get a list of required words, components and bank them.<br>
<br>
A posse of 5 mages sounds very cool.  I don't know how powerful you are at that level so I may be suggesting places too dangerous for you, but you might have to try them out.<br>
