<br>
I've done a few 4 mage/1 necro and 5 mage groups with one other. They are a blast.<br>
<br>
2) At your level, I loved water pets. Fire is probably a good idea too. The times I was in a 4+ mage group, we all summoned air pets and gave them gnoll hide lariats (stun whips). The mobs were SO stunned.<br>
<br>
4) I've fought in Stonebrunt as a necro/monk from 20-40+. There are several kobold camps around the zone in and you can get solo pulls from them. I don't know if there will be enough for your group between all the camps or not.<br>
<br>
The only other areas I found to have a lot of mobs were in the northern part of the zone with the snow.  There are two separate kobold camps fairly far apart from one another.  Both have roamers around them.  The one to the east (I believe its the east) has a lot of roamers and you couldn't run out.  I started soloing the northern camps around 27, I believe.  The roamers are higher level than the camps and some of them can hit quite hard (monk soloed the roamers into the low 40s and was decently twinked).  I believe some of the roamers can also run quite fast, but I don't remember for certain since it has been quite a while since I hunted in this zone.<br>
<br>
6) I tried practice research and to be honest, it sucks. It is poorly designed and takes a long time to collect enough items to get a few skill ups. <br>
<br>
I recommend either of two things. First and least expensive is to gather the required spell components and find a high level mage that isn't busy and has a high research skill. Most mages with a high skill will be willing to do the combines for free provided you supply the components and the book to make them. If you are on the Tribunal, look me up if you choose this path. I have a 183 research skill and rarely fail (though it does happen now and then due to the 5% chance that is always present).<br>
<br>
The other path would be to save up on money and train five points into research each time you level. This gets fairly expensive at higher levels. This is the path I took and stopped training points once I'd made all of the 49th pets. I've heard many of our research pets are for sale in Katta. I can't verify this myself since I'm a dark elf and they refuse to sell to me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
