<br>
Target was Netherbian lair.  (we tend to target zones, just easier that way)<br>
<br>
At entry we had 2 lvl 20 and 3 lvl 19, all the 19's had lvl 20 spells on hand.  Set up 5 fire pets, too a few fungiod for exp/practice and started pulling.<br>
<br>
Early on we got a Trog King, with 2 or 3 adds (I think 3, but wasn't counting).  No deaths, no pet deaths (but close).  With that done we knew we could stay.  Also we got 2 more lvl 20's soon after.<br>
<br>
With some odd pathing we chose to move into the tunnels.  We had recently been buffed by high level players stopped by the odd sight of 5 gnome magicians all in lime-green.  As puller I don't think I stopped for more that an occasional pet heal the entire run.  I watched very few fights,  just sent in my pet and went looking for the next target.  <br>
<br>
All 5 of us gained over 4 yellow bubbles of exp in our 2 hours of playing, and a good time was had by all.  Loot was acceptable, with decent cash/words as well as 2 soiled breechclouts and some weaponry (spears and hammers).<br>
<br>
Considering that many of the pulls were yellow and/or red and quite a few were multiple I think we can safely say the &quot;pet squad&quot; theory is well proven up to and including lvl 20. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If you have the opportunity to get some friends together and try this yourselves, I must say I haven't been disappointed yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
